<h3>The Home Row is Good. Your Mouse is Evil.
</h3>
We've all been told to, "Click File, then Save As, blah blah blah."

With a few simple steps, you can access a menu really quickly, and never touch your mouse. Â Ready?

<ol>
	
<li>
<span style="line-height:1.714285714;font-size:1rem;">
<strong>Cmd+?
</strong> (Cmd+Shift+/) - This will bring up the Help menu.
</span>
</li>
	
<li>
<span style="line-height:1.714285714;font-size:1rem;">Start typing the Menu Item you want to "click", such as "
<strong>Sav
</strong>" for "Save as"
</span>
</li>
	
<li>
<span style="line-height:1.714285714;font-size:1rem;">Once you find it, use 
<strong>Ctrl+n
</strong> or 
<strong>Ctrl+p
</strong> to highlight it.
</span>
</li>
	
<li>
<span style="line-height:1.714285714;font-size:1rem;">Press 
<strong>Enter
</strong>.
</span>
</li>

</ol>

<span style="font-size:1rem;line-height:1.714285714;">Winning? =p
</span>
